            "abstractNote": "The observation was conducted in order to identify bats which roost in the caves in Kabupaten Sumbawa, Sumbawa Island. This study was conducted in 10 caves. The results showed that the six caves whisch were roosted by bats, had an average humidity of 88.16% and an average temperature of 80.S1'F, on the other hand the caves which were not roosted by bats had an average humidity of 77.3%, an average temperature of 84.2°F. The bats which roosted in the caves were Rhinolophus acuminatus, R. affinis, Hipposideros diadem a, If. larvatus, Chaeropon plicata, Dobsonia sp., Taphozous melanophogon, Miniopterus pusillus, M. schreibersi, Pipistrellus sp. The data showed that there were 3 groups of bats in the caves, every group was supposed to roost close 10 the others. The first group was R. acuminatus and R. affinis, (X\" < 0.05) that roosted in the part of the cave with a humidityof91.13% and a temperature of 82.4°F. The second group was If. larvatus, H diadem a, Dobsonia sp., T metanophogon, M. pusilus (X2 < 0.05) which roosted in the part of the caves which had a humidity of 80% and a temperature of 81.010F. While the rest were Pipistrcllus sp., M. schreibersi and C. plicata (X2 > 0.05) which preferred a roosting place with a humidity of90.7S% and a temperature of78.3So.",
